s=3D"faq-rhs"><h3 class=3D"faq-item-ques" itemprop=3D"name">What is a Rhomb=
us?</h3><div itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"https:/=
/schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text">
<p>A rhombus is a type of quadrilateral whose opposite sides are parallel a=
nd equal. Also, the opposite angles of a rhombus are equal and the diagonal=
s bisect each other at right angles.</p>
</div></div></div></section><section class=3D"faq-item" itemscope=3D"" item=
prop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><div class=3D"=
faq-num">Q2 </div><div class=3D"faq-rhs"><h3 class=3D"faq-item-ques" itempr=
op=3D"name">What is the Formula for Area of a Rhombus?</h3><div itemprop=3D=
"acceptedAnswer" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div=
 itemprop=3D"text">
<p>To calculate the area of a rhombus, the following formula is used:</p>
<p>A =3D =C2=BD =C3=97 d<sub>1</sub> =C3=97 d<sub>2</sub></p>
</div></div></div></section><section class=3D"faq-item" itemscope=3D"" item=
prop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><div class=3D"=
faq-num">Q3 </div><div class=3D"faq-rhs"><h3 class=3D"faq-item-ques" itempr=
op=3D"name">How to Find the Area of a Rhombus When the Side and Height are =
Given?</h3><div itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"http=
s://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text">
<p>To find the area of a rhombus when the measures of its height and side a=
re given, use the following formula:</p>
<p>A =3D Base =C3=97 Height</p>
</div></div></div></section><section class=3D"faq-item" itemscope=3D"" item=
prop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><div class=3D"=
