op=3D"name">What is the Formula for Perimeter of a Rhombus?</h3><div itempr=
op=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"=
><div itemprop=3D"text">
<p>The formula to calculate the perimeter of a rhombus of side =E2=80=9Ca=
=E2=80=9D is:</p>
<p>P =3D 4a units</p>
</div></div></div></section><section class=3D"faq-item" itemscope=3D"" item=
prop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><div class=3D"=
