<p>If =E2=80=9Ca=E2=80=9D be its sides and =E2=80=9C=CE=B8=E2=80=9D is an i=
ncluded angle, then the formula is:<br>
Area of a Rhombus =3D a<sup>2</sup> sin =CE=B8 square units.</p>
