op=3D"name">Find the area of a rhombus if the diagonal measures 6cm and 4cm=
.</h3><div itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"https://s=
chema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text">
<p>We know that, Area of Rhombus =3D (=C2=BD) =C3=97 Diagonal 1 =C3=97 Diag=
onal 2<br>
Substituting the values, we get<br>
A =3D (=C2=BD) =C3=97 4 =C3=97 6 =3D 12 cm<sup>2</sup>.</p>
</div></div></div></section><section class=3D"faq-item" itemscope=3D"" item=
prop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><div class=3D"=
