op=3D"name">Is the area of a rhombus the same as the area of a square?</h3>=
<div itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"https://schema.=
org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text">
<p>No, the area of a rhombus is not the same as the area of a square.</p>
</div></div></div></section><section class=3D"faq-item" itemscope=3D"" item=
prop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><div class=3D"=
faq-num">Q8 </div><div class=3D"faq-rhs"><h3 class=3D"faq-item-ques" itempr=
op=3D"name">What is the difference between the area of a rhombus and the ar=
ea of a square?</h3><div itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemscope=3D"" itemtyp=
e=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text">
<p>The area of a square is the square of its side, whereas the area of a rh=
ombus is the half the product of diagonal 1 and diagonal 2.</p>
</div></div></div></section></div></div></div>

